# ── WHOOP API (powers the dashboard's "Connect Whoop" button) ──────────────
# 1. Create an app at https://developer.whoop.com  (Developer Dashboard → create app)
# 2. Copy its Client ID + Client Secret into these vars.
# 3. Set them in Vercel → your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#    (and/or in a local .env for `vercel dev`).
# 4. In the WHOOP app settings, register this exact Redirect URL:
#        https://YOUR-APP.vercel.app/api/whoop/callback
#    (for local dev with `vercel dev`: http://localhost:3000/api/whoop/callback)
# The secret stays server-side in the /api functions — it is never sent to the browser.
WHOOP_CLIENT_ID=
WHOOP_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── FITBIT API (powers the dashboard's "Connect Fitbit" button) ────────────
# 1. Register an app at https://dev.fitbit.com/apps/new
#    - OAuth 2.0 Application Type: "Server" (confidential client)
#    - Callback URL: https://YOUR-APP.vercel.app/api/fitbit/callback
#      (for local dev with `vercel dev`: http://localhost:3000/api/fitbit/callback)
#    - Default scopes used: sleep, heartrate, profile
# 2. Copy the app's OAuth 2.0 Client ID + Client Secret into these vars.
# 3. Set them in Vercel → your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#    (and/or in a local .env for `vercel dev`).
# The secret stays server-side in the /api functions — it is never sent to the browser.
FITBIT_CLIENT_ID=
FITBIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
